<title>BRAZIL: Brazil Authorizes Electricity Tariff rise.</title>
<headline>Brazil Authorizes Electricity Tariff rise.</headline>
<dateline>BRASILIA 1997-04-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Brazilian government has authorized a increase in electricity tariffs averaging 9.92 percent, a spokesman for the Mines and Energy Ministry said.</p>
<p>The increase will become affective April 8 and was the first rise in power tariffs since November 1995, the spokesman said.</p>
<p>The increases would vary from region to region and represented a 6.9 percent rise in annual terms given that no increase had been authorized for the past 17 months, he said.</p>
<p>((--Brazilian newsroom 5561-223-0358))</p>
